cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the deployment of base stations for wireless access, which is a networking issue. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the concept of channel capacity, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the on-off transmission strategy of base stations, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the stability and performance of the wireless access system, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses mathematical models and analysis to solve an engineering problem, which can be seen as a computational engineering problem.
